			<node ID="ID_1126453789" TEXT="Breadth First Search (BFS) There are many ways to traverse graphs. BFS is the most commonly used approach. BFS is a traversing algorithm where you should start traversing from a selected node (source or starting node) and traverse the graph layerwise thus exploring the neighbour nodes (nodes which are directly connected to source node)." />
			</node>
