			<node ID="ID_1313372273" TEXT="Lets say that we can find a hash function h(k) which maps most of the keys onto unique integers but maps a small number of keys on to the same integer. If the number of collisions (cases where multiple keys map onto the same integer) is sufficiently small then hash tables work quite well and give O(1) search times. Handling the collisions" />
