			<node ID="ID_255777580" TEXT="A critical statistic for a hash table is the load factor defined as = where n is the number of entries occupied in the hash table. k is the number of buckets. As the load factor grows larger the hash table becomes slower and it may even fail to work (depending on the method used)." />
