			<node ID="ID_1548517848" TEXT="ISAM (an acronym for indexed sequential access method) is a method for creating maintaining and manipulating computer files of data so that records can be retrieved sequentially or randomly by one or more keys.Indexes of key fields are maintained to achieve fast retrieval of required file records in Indexed files. IBM originally developed ISAM for mainframe computers but implementations are " />
			</node>
